It is unconscionable that our air traffic controllers, TSA agents, border patrol, & other dedicated employees are set to miss a 2nd paycheck. The House has voted 10 times to reopen the govt. I urge every Senator to support the CR that would reopen the govt and #EndTheShutdownNow

Today I again voted to reopen the Federal Government. Every day the government remains shuttered, the consequences become more severe and the burden placed on federal workers and contractors becomes heavier.

Hundreds of food inspectors have been furloughed, putting our food safety at risk.
Small farmers can’t get access to loans to buy supplies for 2019, potentially disrupting an entire year of planting.
The FDA is unable to review new prescription drugs, delaying potentially lifesaving treatment from getting to those who need them.

Gun violence isn’t just mass shootings. Nearly 40,000 Americans died last year as a result of gun violence, some in our own backyard. I’m proud to join Democrats in introducing commonsense background check laws. #EndGunViolence #NeverAgain pic.twitter.com/0DR4SQocH9

It’s time for Congressional Republicans and the President to join us in reopening the government now. Let’s have a debate about border security and about comprehensive immigration reform, but let’s do it with the government open instead of taking the America people hostage.
Last night, the President used fear tactics instead of facts, as @SpeakerPelosi said. The new House majority has already passed legislation that would end the shutdown.

The American people are already feeling the effects of the govt shutdown & it will only get worse if it continues. Yesterday, I met an air traffic controller at Bradley Airport who is going w/o pay to keep the traveling public safe. Many of his colleagues have been furloughed.
It makes no sense to shutdown the government and not pay the very people in charge of protecting our borders. It’s time to reopen the government and pay our workers what they’ve earned.

It’s time to reopen government. The House passed legislation last week to do just that and fund Homeland Security, the IRS, the FAA and more. The House will act again this week. I won’t stop fighting until the government is reopened. #EndTheShutdown

Bryan works at Bradley Tower in Windsor Locks where 40 controllers are working hard without pay to keep the traveling public safe. That’s in addition to FAA aviation specialists who are furloughed. #ShutdownStories
It was a pleasure meeting Air Traffic Controllers Bryan Krampovitis and Kevin Coeyman, who are keeping our airways safe without a paycheck during the #Shutdown. pic.twitter.com/4qbsNFDMS3

Today I voted to re-open the govt. From the beginning, workers have been political pawns. The House, led by Democrats has approved legislation that re-opens the govt. It’s time for this shutdown to end & for us to get to work. https://larson.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/larson-it-s-time-open-government-and-get-back-work …

I was also especially proud to support @SpeakerPelosi today. She is the first woman and first Italian-American to be Speaker of the House. She has been an strong leader on climate change, election reform, health care, and Social Security, and a dear friend for many years.

Today, the People’s House returned to the people. Over the past 2 yrs Americans have used their voices to stop the repeal of the ACA & elect dozens of Democrats to the halls of Congress. We will restore regular order and bring on commonsense solutions to help the American people.
